passages.text: August 31, 2025 07:45 PM GMT
Marine Transportation | Japan
Container Spot Rates (CCF) Out of China (Aug 29): Downside Risk to ONE's NP Guidance for Jul-Sep 2025 a Concern

Simple average spot freight rate for Jul-Aug 2025 down by an estimated \(6\%\) QoQ on North America routes and up \(3\%\) QoQ on Europe routes. We expect the downward trend in spot freight rates to continue, driven by ongoing vessel oversupply. According to the National Retail Federation, container import volume for Jul-Sep 2025 is projected to increase by only \(3\%\) QoQ. Meanwhile, ONE's revenue forecast for Jul-Sep 2025 is a \(17\%\) QoQ increase, with NP projected at \(\) 464\mathrm{mn}\(compared to NP of\) \ \(86\mathrm{mn}\) in Apr-Jun 2025. Considering the risk of rising unit costs, there is concern that ONE's NP forecast for Jul-Sep 2025 may be subject to downside risk.

CCFI rates as of Aug 29 were - 3.1% week- over- week & - 44.6% year- over- year on N. America routes to the west coast, and - 1.6% WoW & - 42.6% YoY to the east coast. Rates on Europe routes were - 4.1% WoW & - 52.9% YoY to northern Europe, and - 1.1% WoW & - 46.1% YoY to Mediterranean locations.
